label: potential density
definition: A density which would inhere in a bearer if such bearer were adiabatically brought to a standard reference pressure.

label: electrical resistivity
editors note: TO ADD to PATO inverse of conductivity see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrical_resistivity_and_conductivity

label: salinity
definition: An osmolarity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the total amount of ionic salts dissolved in the bearer.
editors note: Waiting for PR to be approved and merged in PATO.

label: potential temperature
definition: A temperature which would inhere in a bearer if such bearer were adiabatically compressed from it's existing temperature and pressure to a standard presure.
